@database scenearc3
@node MAIN
@title "The Scene Archives disklist"

                    *** THE SCENE ARCHIVES DISKLIST ***

    CONTENTS:
    =========

    @{"Animations" link ANIMATIONS}
    @{"Demo Packs" link PACKS}
    @{"Dentros & 40K Intros" link DENTROS}
    @{"Digis" link DIGIS}
    @{"Intros" link INTROS}
    @{"Magazines" link MAGAZINES}
    @{"Menus" link MENUS}
    @{"Miscellaneous" link MISC}
    @{"Music Disks" link MUSIC}
    @{"Slideshow" link SLIDESHOW}
    @{"Trackmos" link TRACKMOS}

    @{"How to Contact me" link CONTACT}


    KEY:-
    =====
    
    The column headers typically look like :-

 Name                                 Makers               # Number    AGA HD MG
|------------------------------------|--------------------|-|---------|---|--|--

    Where:-
        Name   - Name of Production
        Makers - Who Made it
        #      - Number of Disks
        Number - Where it is
        AGA    - The Product needs AGA to run
        HD     - The Product has to be installed onto Hard-drive for it to run
        MG     - The Product needs x amount of Fast Memory to run
                 Where :-
                    xM = Need x meg in total (Don't Matter is chip/fast)
                    xC = Need x meg of Chip Memory
                    xF = Need x meg of Fast Memory

    Note: Any thing with the number of Disks at 0, this means that it is an REALLY 
Large productions (more than 10 disks). 

@endnode


